ej.wadapps.admin

Interface Application


  • public interface Application
    An application represents a deployment unit.

    Two applications are equals if and only if they have the same identifier.

      • start

        void start()
    throws IllegalStateException,
           SecurityException,
           ApplicationOperationException
        Causes this application to start. A new thread owned by the application is created and started. The application is switched in the Application.State.STARTED state and this method returns.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if the application state is not Application.State.INSTALLED state.
        SecurityException - if a security manager exits and if the caller does not have the appropriate permissions.
        ApplicationOperationException - If any unexpected errors occur while starting this application.

      • start

        void start(IProgressMonitor monitor)
    throws IllegalStateException,
           SecurityException,
           ApplicationOperationException
        Causes this application to start. A new thread owned by the application is created and started. The application is switched in the Application.State.STARTED state and this method returns.
        Parameters:
        monitor - the progress monitor to use for reporting progress to the user. It is the caller's responsibility to call done() on the given monitor. Accepts null, indicating that no progress should be reported and that the operation cannot be cancelled.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if the application state is not Application.State.INSTALLED state.
        SecurityException - if a security manager exits and if the caller does not have the appropriate permissions.
        ApplicationOperationException - If any unexpected errors occur while starting this application.

      • stop

        void stop()
   throws IllegalStateException,
          SecurityException,
          ApplicationOperationException
        Causes this application to stop. The application is switched in the Application.State.INSTALLED state and this method returns.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if the application is in the Application.State.INSTALLED or Application.State.UNINSTALLED state.
        SecurityException - if a security manager exits and if the caller does not have the appropriate permissions.
        ApplicationOperationException - If any unexpected errors occur while stopping this application.
